By Olawale Ajimotokan Hoodlums Monday morning brazenly looted relief palliatives after breaking into another warehouse in Gwagwalada, in Gwagwalada Area Council of FCT. The warehouse, near West African Examination Council (WAEC) office, is said to contain items belonging to the Federal Capital Territory Administration (FCTA). Some of the hoodlums carted away bags of rice and cartons of noodles, cartons of milk and tin tomatoes among others. Some of the items were taken away on motorcycles and tricycles. Details laterâ€¦